President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2014 as Jewish American Heritage Month in the United States. In the proclamation, he highlights the contributions of Jewish Americans in various fields and their historical struggles. He also emphasizes the common cause between Jewish Americans and the Civil Rights Movement, and the need to combat anti-Semitism and promote tolerance. The proclamation also reaffirms the strong bond between the United States and Israel. President Obama calls upon all Americans to learn more about the heritage and contributions of Jewish Americans and to observe the month with appropriate programs and activities.